  "prompt": "My cellphone shows two icons of one app. How can I remove it?",
  "response": "To remove duplicate app icons on your phone, try these steps:\n\n1. For Android:\n- Go to Settings\n- Find \"Apps\" or \"App Management\"\n- Tap on the duplicate app\n- Select \"Uninstall\" or \"Disable\"\n- Or long-press the duplicate icon on home screen and drag to \"Uninstall\"\n\n2. For iPhone:\n- Long-press the duplicate app icon\n- Tap \"Remove App\"\n- Choose \"Delete App\"\n\nIf these don't work, you might try:\n- Clearing app cache\n- Restarting your phone\n- Reinstalling the app\n- Checking for system updates\n\nWould you like me to provide more specific steps for your phone's brand/model?",
